The paper discusses a toy-model of publications and citations processes, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, the paper discusses the rating of scientific publications, which is related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper touches on the role of randomness in the processes, which is a topic that could be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, and cs.SD, in that order.
